                                         ACTIVATE TOUCH SCREEN

STEPS:

on Raspberry side: 
1)
 www.waveshare.com/w/upload/9/9d/LCD-show-151020.tar.gz

2)
On Terminal
sudo nano /boot/config.txt
 enter screen conf. dimension for example in 5 inches screen 800x480 enter the text below
"
max_usb_current=1
hdmi_group=2
hdmi_mode=87
hdmi_cvt 800 480 60 6 0 0 0
"

3)
go to Download folder "cd Download" ( or go to the folder you download the .gz file ) 
and excecute the .gz file  
example ->" tar xzvf /boot/LCD-show-YYMMDD.tar.gz "

4)
NOT COMMAND LINE
go to /home/pi/Downloads/LCD-show or whatever your file location. Open that folder and edit "cmdline.txt" file... from "root=/dev/mmcblkop2" - "root=/dev/mmcblkop7" .

5)
COMMAND LINE 
cd /home/pi/Downloads/LCD-show   (if it is located on Download folder)
sudo ./LCD-show  example (sudo ./LCD5-show)
